{"TopicId":155348,"ForumId":36,"TopicTitle":"[WIP] [1.3] SpeedUnitDisplay 0.2","CreatedByName":"ThirdOfSeven","CreatedById":135015,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-21T11:41:33Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"ThirdOfSeven","CreatedById":135015,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-21T11:41:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPresenting my first mod for Kerbal Space Program.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, almost my, because it is too much inspired by \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/68202-12-speed-unit-changer-ap-pe-on-your-navball/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003ESpeedUnitChanger\u003C/a\u003E by @\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Ca data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/49289-lttito/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0026amp;referrer=http%253A%252F%252Fforum.kerbalspaceprogram.com%252Findex.php%253F%252Ftopic%252F68202-12-speed-unit-changer-ap-pe-on-your-navball%252F\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/49289-lttito/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022 title=\u0022Go to lttito\u0027s profile\u0022\u003Elttito\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat it does: noting complicated. No configuration, no buttons, it just changes your Surface speed indicator to this one:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022SpeedUnitDisplay.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022https://raw.githubusercontent.com/stasikos/SpeedUnitDisplay/master/SpeedUnitDisplay.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy? IAS is what I\u0027m missing so much in all mods. But no mod show it together with true speed, even \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aerospace Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E. And it is very interesting to know IAS when you play with planes very often. Also I added km/h display to somehow rely on IRL performances without doing simple arithmetics all the time. It is quite small display, probably, so I\u0027m open to any suggestions how to improve it while keeping all information visible to player.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCurrently it is unknown if it is working with Ferram Aerospace Research properly (in terms of IAS value).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGitHub: \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/stasikos/SpeedUnitDisplay\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/stasikos/SpeedUnitDisplay\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReleases page (GitHub): \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/stasikos/SpeedUnitDisplay/releases\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/stasikos/SpeedUnitDisplay/releases\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLicense: GPLv3 (derived)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-06-01T22:24:00Z\u0022 title=\u002206/01/2017 10:24  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJune 1, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by ThirdOfSeven\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HardCosmosOrg.","CreatedById":174051,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-21T16:01:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMOLODEC!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou maked compile on old releses KSP? (1.1.x or 1.0.x)\u00A0I do not know much English \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E Translator to help!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ThirdOfSeven","CreatedById":135015,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-21T18:25:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222929540\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155348\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221485014465\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022174051\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022HardCosmosOrg.\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, HardCosmosOrg. said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMOLODEC!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou maked compile on old releses KSP? (1.1.x or 1.0.x)\u00A0I do not know much English \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E Translator to help!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUnfortunately I don\u0027t have 1.1.x or 1.0.x version to check. But it doesn\u0027t use any complex/new APIs, so, it is probably will compile against.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HardCosmosOrg.","CreatedById":174051,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-22T19:21:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222929694\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155348\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221485023144\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022135015\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ThirdOfSeven\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 21.01.2017 at 9:25 PM, ThirdOfSeven said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUnfortunately I don\u0027t have 1.1.x or 1.0.x version to check. But it doesn\u0027t use any complex/new APIs, so, it is probably will compile against.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ThirdOfSeven","CreatedById":135015,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-01T22:23:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFixed and recompiled for 1.3. Planning to change way it works by moving speeds out of navball, cause it is quite small place to show so much information. Or make it configurable, probably.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, it is obvious, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aerospace Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E will require another change to get correct values to display.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}